	</div>
	<div align="center" class="main-content">
		<div class="spacer">
	</div><br>			<label class="collapse_ACT" for="_1"><font size="5px">BolA transcriptional activity</font></label>
				<input id="_1" type="checkbox">
				<div class="ACT"><br><ul><li>The GrxD homodimer and GrxD-BolA heterodimer complexes are both capable of intact transfer of their FeS cluster to the model client protein apoferredoxin ( Fdx ) in 2 The abbreviations used are : AdoMet , S-adenosylmethionine ; Isc , iron sulfur cluster biosynthesis system ; Suf , sulfur utilization factor biosynthesis system ; Nif , nitrogen fixation biosynthesis system ; i6A , the modified nucleoside N6-isopentenyl adenosine ; ms2i6A , the modified nucleoside 2-meth-ylthio-N6-isopentenyl adenosine ; Fdx , ferredoxin ; Grx , glutaredoxin ; SPA , Sequential peptide affinity ; AcnB , aconitase B ; ESI , electrospray mass ionization .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=23543739" target="_blank">23543739</a>]<br></li>
<li>ibaG is Not Regulated by BolA but Seems to Require its Presence for Regular Transcription According to the previous results , ibaG and bolA seem to concur in distinct pathways .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=22534295" target="_blank">22534295</a>]<br></li>
<li>Furthermore , a permanent role for BolA as a transcriptional-regulator of PBP5 , PBP6 , and the b-lactamase AmpC is unravelled , for the ﬁrst time linking PBPs and b-lactamases at the level of gene regulation .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12354237" target="_blank">12354237</a>]<br></li>
<li>BolA affects growth and binds to the promoters of penicillin-binding proteins 5 and 6 regulating their expression .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=22534295" target="_blank">22534295</a>]<br></li>
<li>When present in high-copy-number vectors , bolA + does not need an upstream strong promoter to produce its characteristic morphological effects , while maxicell experiments have shown that BolA synthesis regulated by its promoter is own almost efficient it is when regulated by the tet as as promoter , suggesting that bolA could be tightly repressed under normal conditions during exponential-growth .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=3053647" target="_blank">3053647</a>]<br></li>
<li>shown to be necessary to maintain regular ibaG transcriptional levels , with a strong emphasis in the stationary phase of growth , when BolA is normally present in increased concentrations .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=22534295" target="_blank">22534295</a>]<br></li>
<li>Particularly , BolA could be directly involved in the FtsZ-dependen increase in carboxypeptidase activity that takes place immediately before cell division ( 31 , 32 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=3053647" target="_blank">3053647</a>]<br></li>
<li>The absence of bolA-mediated morphology when septation is inhibited before bolA induction ( Fig. 1b1 and b2 ) indicates two possibi-lities : ( a ) the cells might be committed to an irrever-sible morphological pathway by the influence of aztreonam and BolA is no longer able to induce a rounder shape or ( b ) BolA-dependent inhibition of elongation might require a functional septation machinery , here inhibited by blocking PBP3 , at least in an initial phase .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19111750" target="_blank">19111750</a>]<br></li>
<li>BolA prevents cellular elongation/rod shape maintenance mechanisms Cefmetazole is a cephalosporin that inhibits all E. coli PBPs except PBP2 .13 This antibiotic was used simultaneously with aztreonam in a similar expe-riment as in Fig. 1 to inhibit all PBP functions , except for PBP2 , and focus the analysis of the effect of bolA on elongation mechanisms , independently of PBP5 or PBP6 , previously shown to be regulated by BolA .11 The results were generally the same as those illustrated in Fig. 1 , showing that bolA overexpression is unable to revert the filament morphology when septation is blocked before its own induction ( Fig. 2d1 and d2 ) and that cells are unable to elongate when bolA is overexpressed prior to septation inhibition ( Fig. 2e1 and e2 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19111750" target="_blank">19111750</a>]<br></li>
<li>MreB concentration in fast-growing cells reaches 40,000 molecules/cell ; in slow-growing cells , it was estimated at 17,000 molecules/cell .14 Inversely , bolA mRNA levels are low in fast-growing cells but increase by about 20-fold in slow-growing cells ; 4 the regulation of BolA expression might therefore be connected to the differential expression of MreB during different growth-phases .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19111750" target="_blank">19111750</a>]<br></li>
<li>Edited by J. Karn Keywords : BolA ; MreB ; transcriptional-repressor ; morphology ; cytoskeleton Penicillin-binding proteins ( PBPs ) are key players in cell elongation and division mechanisms .1 In Escherichia coli , PBP2 is responsible for lateral murein extension , leading to cell elongation , while PBP3 is specific for septal murein production during cell division .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19111750" target="_blank">19111750</a>]<br></li>
<li>MreB is a structural homolog of actin that is also essential for cell elongation and maintenance of a bacterial rod shape .2,3 The morphogene bolA induces a spherical shape when overexpressed , and it has been established as a general stress response gene .4 The expression of bolA is tightly controlled .5 -- 7 bolA increases biofilm formation8 and modulates cell permeability ; 9 in addition , it was demonstrated that bolA increases the expression of PBP5 , PBP6 and ampC mRNA .10,11 In this work , we analyzed the effect of BolA on cell growth and elongation using a set of specific anti-biotics that induce known morphology alterations * Corresponding author .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19111750" target="_blank">19111750</a>]<br></li>
<li>The conjugated effects of BolA in MreB , PBP5 , and PBP6 thus contribute to induce the round morphology in PBP single mutants .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19111750" target="_blank">19111750</a>]<br></li>
<li>An increase in BolA leads to a significant reduction in MreB protein levels and mreB transcripts .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19111750" target="_blank">19111750</a>]<br></li>
<li>The finding that BolA can directly repress the transcription of mreBCD and lower the levels of MreB in the cell presents a broad impact on cellular features , such a morphology maintenance and elongation mechan-isms , especially in stress conditions when bolA is induced .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19111750" target="_blank">19111750</a>]<br></li>
<li>Even though MreB overexpression can not revert the morphology induced by BolA , higher levels of MreB in the cell clearly impair the induction of a rounder/shorter shape by BolA .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19111750" target="_blank">19111750</a>]<br></li>
<li>The induction of PBP5 and PBP6 and the reduction in MreB levels by BolA overexpression converge to inhibit cell elongation and induce a rounder morphology .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19111750" target="_blank">19111750</a>]<br></li>
<li>Results presented in this report show that increased BolA levels can inhibit cell elongation mechanisms .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19111750" target="_blank">19111750</a>]<br></li>
<li>Freire P , Moreira RN , Arraino CM ( 2009 ) BolA inhibits cell elongation and regulates MreB expression levels .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=23708427" target="_blank">23708427</a>]<br></li>
<li>S1 ) , demonstrating that overexpression of ( His ) 6 -- BolA induces the same cellular morphology alterations that are observed when the native BolA protein is overexpressed .4 Two hours after induction of BolA , the optical density at 620 nm ( OD620 ) of the culture increased 2.5 × ; without induction of bolA , the OD620 increased 7 × ( data not shown ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19111750" target="_blank">19111750</a>]<br></li>
<li>After 2 h of induction , when only BolA was overexpressed in the BL21 + pPFA02 strain , cells became spherical or lemon-shaped .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19111750" target="_blank">19111750</a>]<br></li>
				</div></ul><br>
			<label class="collapse_DOM" for="_2"><font size="5px">BolA protein domains</font></label>
				<input id="_2" type="checkbox">
				<div class="DOM"><br><ul><li>The underlined protein sequences of BolA indicate a putative DNA-binding domain .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=2684651" target="_blank">2684651</a>]<br></li>
<li>However , an helix ± turn ± helix motif found in the protein sequence , which could correspond to a DNA-binding domain , and data obtained by two-dimensional protein electrophoresis led to the suggestion that BolA can induce , at the transcription level , the synthesis of a penicillin-binding protein ( PBP6 ) ( Aldea et al. , 1989 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10361282" target="_blank">10361282</a>]<br></li>
<li>that bolA is an inducing factor for A putative DNA-binding domain has been found in BolA , suggesting that the proposed increase in the rate of synthesis of PBP6 caused by BolA takes place at the level of transcription .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=2684651" target="_blank">2684651</a>]<br></li>
<li>We determined a Kd of 6.9 ± 2.4 nM for BolA interaction with mreB promo-ters and a Kd of 23.6 ± 5.4 nM for the interaction with the bolA orf .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19111750" target="_blank">19111750</a>]<br></li>
<li>In the case of BolA , no interaction with MiaB was observed by SPR despite indication of a weak interaction by co-purification .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=23543739" target="_blank">23543739</a>]<br></li>
<li>In addition , over 70 % of the amino acid residues of both the BolA and YrbA proteins can be aligned .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=22534295" target="_blank">22534295</a>]<br></li>
<li>In common with BolA , YrbA has a helix-turn-helix motif , usually responsible for protein-DNA interaction .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=22534295" target="_blank">22534295</a>]<br></li>
				</div></ul><br>
			<label class="collapse_RP" for="_4"><font size="5px">Processes regulated by BolA</font></label>
				<input id="_4" type="checkbox">
				<div class="RP"><br><ul><li>( 2009 ) 385 , 1345 -- 1351 Available online at www.sciencedirect.com C OMMUNICA TION BolA Inhibits Cell Elongation and Regulates MreB xpression Levels E aria Arraiano Patrick Freire , Ricardo Neves Moreira and Cecília M Control of Gene Expression Laboratory , Instituto de Tecnologia Química e Biológica / Universidade Nova de Lisboa , Apartado 127 , Av .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19111750" target="_blank">19111750</a>]<br></li>
<li>BolA overexpression induces biofilm-formation [ 34 ] , and alters outer membrane properties , namely accessibility and sensitivity towards detergents and antibiotics [ 13 ] .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=22534295" target="_blank">22534295</a>]<br></li>
<li>Furthermore , a permanent role for BolA as a transcriptional regulator of PBP5 , PBP6 , and the b-lactamase AmpC is unravelled , for the ﬁrst time linking PBPs and b-lactamases at the level of gene regulation .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12354237" target="_blank">12354237</a>]<br></li>
<li>Edited by J. Karn Keywords : BolA ; MreB ; transcriptional repressor ; morphology ; cytoskeleton Penicillin-binding proteins ( PBPs ) are key players in cell-elongation and division mechanisms .1 In Escherichia coli , PBP2 is responsible for lateral murein extension , leading to cell-elongation , while PBP3 is specific for septal murein production during cell-division .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19111750" target="_blank">19111750</a>]<br></li>
<li>BolA is thus shown to act as a new negative regulator of MreB .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19111750" target="_blank">19111750</a>]<br></li>
<li>BolA therefore seems to play a central role in a complex web of regulators of cell morphology/elongation that includes PBP5 , PBP6 , MreB , and probably other factors .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19111750" target="_blank">19111750</a>]<br></li>
<li>Results show that BolA inhibits the mechanism of cell-elongation and can act as a new transcriptional repressor of MreB expression .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19111750" target="_blank">19111750</a>]<br></li>
<li>Freire P , Moreira RN , Arraino CM ( 2009 ) BolA inhibits cell-elongation and regulates MreB expression levels .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=23708427" target="_blank">23708427</a>]<br></li>
<li>BolA inhibits cell-elongation and regulates MreB expression levels .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=22534295" target="_blank">22534295</a>]<br></li>
<li>MreB is a structural homolog of actin that is also essential for cell-elongation and maintenance of a bacterial rod shape .2,3 The morphogene bolA induces a spherical shape when overexpressed , and it has been established as a general stress response gene .4 The expression of bolA is tightly controlled .5 -- 7 bolA increases biofilm-formation8 and modulates cell permeability ; 9 in addition , it was demonstrated that bolA increases the expression of PBP5 , PBP6 and ampC mRNA .10,11 In this work , we analyzed the effect of BolA on cell-growth and elongation using a set of specific anti-biotics that induce known morphology alterations * Corresponding author .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19111750" target="_blank">19111750</a>]<br></li>
<li>Therefore , BolA overexpression either blocks PBP2-dependent cell-elongation or affects another mechanism involved in the normal maintenance of the rod shape and essential for elongation .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19111750" target="_blank">19111750</a>]<br></li>
<li>Overexpression of PBP2 was shown to be unable to revert the round phenotype caused by bolA overexpression back to a bacilli shape .10 BolA might then be affecting other elements involved in cell-elongation mechanisms that indirectly impair PBP2-dependent cell-elongation .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19111750" target="_blank">19111750</a>]<br></li>
<li>Particularly , BolA could be directly involved in the FtsZ-dependen increase in carboxypeptidase activity that takes place immediately before cell-division ( 31 , 32 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=3053647" target="_blank">3053647</a>]<br></li>
<li>GrxD can form FeS cluster-containing complexes as both a homodimer and a heterodimer with BolA ( 10 , 11 ) , a poorly characterized protein involved in cell morphology and resistance to stress ( 12 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=23543739" target="_blank">23543739</a>]<br></li>
