				<div class="TU"><br><ul><li>Expression of dacC is induced upon entry into the stationary phase by BolA ( Santos et al. , 2002 ) under the regulation of the low-density lipoprotein receptor related protein ( an apolipoprotein E binding protein ) ( Tani et al. , 2002 ) , but is also upregulated under basic conditions with oxygen limitation ( Hayes et al. , 2006 ) and upon treatment with cefsulodin and amdino-cillin ( Laubacher & Ades , 2008 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=23912810" target="_blank">23912810</a>]<br></li>
<li>ibaG is Not Regulated by BolA but Seems to Require its Presence for Regular Transcription According to the previous results , ibaG and bolA seem to concur in distinct pathways .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=22534295" target="_blank">22534295</a>]<br></li>
<li>Conversely , ibaG is only properly transcribed when BolA is present .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=22534295" target="_blank">22534295</a>]<br></li>
<li>The levels of induced BolA were determined by quantitative Western blot and are provided as supplementary data ( Fig .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19111750" target="_blank">19111750</a>]<br></li>
<li>When present in high-copy-number vectors , bolA + does not need an upstream strong promoter to produce its characteristic morphological effects , while maxicell experiments have shown that BolA synthesis regulated by its promoter is own almost efficient it is when regulated by the tet as as promoter , suggesting that bolA could be tightly repressed under normal conditions during exponential growth .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=3053647" target="_blank">3053647</a>]<br></li>
<li>MreB concentration in fast-growing cells reaches 40,000 molecules/cell ; in slow-growing cells , it was estimated at 17,000 molecules/cell .14 Inversely , bolA mRNA levels are low in fast-growing cells but increase by about 20-fold in slow-growing cells ; 4 the regulation of BolA expression might therefore be connected to the differential expression of MreB during different growth phases .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19111750" target="_blank">19111750</a>]<br></li>
<li>BolA is therefore ( ) Measurements on the inducible strain BL21 + pPFA02 + pRMA02 , A bolA at 0 ( OD 0.5 ) , 30 , and 60 min after addition of either glucose ( repressing bolA leakage expression ) or IPTG ( inducing bolA ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=22534295" target="_blank">22534295</a>]<br></li>
<li>The bolA gene product as a possible inducing factor of a CPase Although the bolA gene did not seem to be autoregulated , we decided to test whether the BolA protein was involved in the expression of other proteins during the transition to the stationary phase ( Groat et al. , 1986 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=2684651" target="_blank">2684651</a>]<br></li>
<li>We have identified two distinct transcription start points for the bolA gene and , by using protein and operon fusions to lacZ , have shown that transcription of bolA increases > 50-fold and synthesis of the BolA protein increases 10-fold during the transition to the stationary phase of growth .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=2684651" target="_blank">2684651</a>]<br></li>
<li>Lanes 1 -- 3 show the results for the strains without bolA overexpression , while lanes 4 -- 6 show MreB levels in the same conditions but with overexpression of bolA using plasmid pMAK580 ( containing bolA with native promoters ) as described previously .11 BolA represses operon mreBCD transcription by direct binding to its promoters A plasmid pRMA1 was constructed containing the gfp gene encoding green fluorescent protein under the control of the promoters of the mreBCD operon using vector p363 .20 Total protein was extracted as above , with and without overexpression of BolA , and green fluorescent protein fluorescence was quantified in a Varian-Eclipse fluorescence spectrophotometer .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19111750" target="_blank">19111750</a>]<br></li>
<li>bolA may encode a regulatory protein that affects carboxypeptidase activity and its expression is inversely regulated by growth rate via the RpoS Sigma factor ( Lange and Hengge-Aronis , 1991a ) , We therefore tested whether either BolA or RpoS affected transcription from the promoter for the ampG operon , and found that they did not .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8231804" target="_blank">8231804</a>]<br></li>
<li>BolA affects the mreBCD operon in vivo at the level of transcription .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19111750" target="_blank">19111750</a>]<br></li>
<li>BolA overexpression is therefore able to shut down transcription of mreBCD operon in vivo to about 64 % of its normal expression , in correlation with the levels of mreB RNA detected above .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19111750" target="_blank">19111750</a>]<br></li>
<li>S1 ) , demonstrating that overexpression of ( His ) 6 -- BolA induces the same cellular morphology alterations that are observed when the native BolA protein is overexpressed .4 Two hours after induction of BolA , the optical density at 620 nm ( OD620 ) of the culture increased 2.5 × ; without induction of bolA , the OD620 increased 7 × ( data not shown ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19111750" target="_blank">19111750</a>]<br></li>
<li>MreB is a structural homolog of actin that is also essential for cell elongation and maintenance of a bacterial rod shape .2,3 The morphogene bolA induces a spherical shape when overexpressed , and it has been established as a general stress response gene .4 The expression of bolA is tightly controlled .5 -- 7 bolA increases biofilm formation8 and modulates cell permeability ; 9 in addition , it was demonstrated that bolA increases the expression of PBP5 , PBP6 and ampC mRNA .10,11 In this work , we analyzed the effect of BolA on cell growth and elongation using a set of specific anti-biotics that induce known morphology alterations * Corresponding author .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19111750" target="_blank">19111750</a>]<br></li>
<li>BolA plays a central role in a morphogenetic pathway including PBP5 , PBP6 , and MreB BolA induces the expression levels of PBP5 and PBP6 at the onset of the exponential phase .11 BolA overexpression was also shown to be unable to promote a round morphology in a PBP5/PBP6 double mutant .11 The inhibition of all PBPs except PBP2 in Fig. 2e1 and e2 shows that bolA is nevertheless able to induce a shorter olive-shaped morphology independently of PBP5 or PBP6 .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19111750" target="_blank">19111750</a>]<br></li>
<li>Furthermore , BolA was also shown to contribute to ampC transcription in exponential phase to approximately the same extent as dacA ( PBP5 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12354237" target="_blank">12354237</a>]<br></li>
